In 2017, [[Square Enix]] released a remake titled ''King's Knight: Wrath of the Dark Dragon'' for [[iOS]] and [[Android (operating system)|Android]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.gematsu.com/2016/09/final-fantasy-xv-universe-game-kings-knight-wrath-dark-dragon-announced-smartphones|title=Final Fantasy XV Universe game King's Knight: Wrath of the Dark Dragon announced for smartphones|date=September 18, 2016|website=Gematsu}}</ref> It was produced by Daisuke Motohashi and developed by Flame Hearts. Developed as a mobile spin-off associated with ''[[Final Fantasy XV]]'', the game borrows the original version's scrolling, action role-playing game style and adds a new camera perspective and an orchestral version of the former's [[chiptune]] soundtrack. The game is [[free-to-play]] with a four-player [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]] mode.<ref name="Polygon: announce">{{cite web |url=http://www.polygon.com/mobile/2016/9/18/12958058/kings-knight-wrath-of-the-dark-dragon-mobile-final-fantasy-trailer |accessdate=September 26, 2016 |title=Final Fantasy 15's latest mobile spinoff is an homage to a 30-year-old game |last=Good |first=Owen S. |work=[[Polygon (website)|Polygon]] |date=September 18, 2016 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160921001001/http://www.polygon.com/mobile/2016/9/18/12958058/kings-knight-wrath-of-the-dark-dragon-mobile-final-fantasy-trailer |archivedate=September 21, 2016 |url-status=live |df=mdy-all}}</ref>

Square Enix announced the game at the September 2016 [[Tokyo Game Show]]. Its promotional material placed the game in the ''[[Final Fantasy XV]]'' universe alongside ''[[Justice Monsters Five]]'', another mobile companion game to the series that Square Enix announced earlier in 2016. ''King's Knight: Wrath of the Dark Dragon'' was planned for release on [[Android (operating system)|Android]] and [[iOS]] platforms in Japan in 2016, with no announcement for a North American release.<ref name="Polygon: announce"/> The game's release was then postponed to 2017.<ref>{{cite web|title=E3 2017: Daisuke Motohashi on What Makes King's Knight – Wrath of the Dark Dragon Essential|url=http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2017/06/20/e3-2017-daisuke-motohashi-on-what-makes-kings-knight-wrath-of-the-dark-dragon-essential/261917/|publisher=Hardcore Gamer|last=Shive|first=Chris|date=June 20, 2017|accessdate=August 21, 2017|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20171004102445/http://www.hardcoregamer.com/2017/06/20/e3-2017-daisuke-motohashi-on-what-makes-kings-knight-wrath-of-the-dark-dragon-essential/261917/|archivedate=October 4, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> It was released worldwide on September 13, but was shut down on June 26, 2018<ref>{{cite tweet|number=978074206352166913|user=FFXVEN|title=We regret to inform you that we will be terminating services for King's Knight at the end of June.We would like to…<!-- full text of tweet that Twitter returned to the bot (excluding links) added by TweetCiteBot. This may be better truncated or may need expanding (TW limits responses to 140 characters) or case changes. --> |date=March 26, 2018}}</ref> - less than a year after its worldwide release.

