In a retrospective review AllGame editor Skyler Miller was critical of the game. Miller noted that "the underlying gameplay is decent" but described the graphics as "elementary" and "the structure of switching characters is awkward and frustrating". Miller noted that the game showed "none of the creativity or innovation that Square would later be known for".<ref name="allgamereview"/>

''King's Knight'' was given a 3/10 on [[IGN]]<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.ign.com/articles/2008/03/26/kings-knight-review|title=King's Knight Review|first=Lucas M.|last=Thomas|date=March 26, 2008|website=ign.com|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20170305091200/http://www.ign.com/articles/2008/03/26/kings-knight-review|archivedate=March 5, 2017|df=mdy-all}}</ref> and 3/10 as well on [[Nintendo Life]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.nintendolife.com/reviews/2008/03/kings_knight_virtual_console|title=Review: King's Knight (Virtual Console / NES)|date=March 25, 2008|website=nintendolife.com|url-status=live|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160918160933/http://www.nintendolife.com/reviews/2008/03/kings_knight_virtual_console|archivedate=September 18, 2016|df=mdy-all}}</ref>

